						<p>
							You can save data to public or private endpoints. Private endpoints are private with respect to the token used to create them. 
							Public endpoints can be <strong>POST</strong>ed to by the owner and consumed by anyone.
						</p>
						<br>
						<h4>
							Private endpoints
						</h4>
						
						<p>
							Private endpoints are created when you <strong>POST</strong> to a user specified path. To create a private endpoint <code>myendpoint</code>, simply
						 <strong>POST</strong> data to <code>/d/myendpoint</code> using your authorization token. This endpoint will be private with respect to the token used to create the endpoint, 
							i.e. if another token is used to <strong>POST</strong> to this endpoint, a seperate private endpoint is created with the same URL but differentiated by the token used to 
							access the data.
						</p>
						
						<br>
						<h4>
							Public endpoints
						</h4>
						
						<p>
							Public endpoints need to generated by the stashy backend and then POSTed to. You can generate a public endpoint on your profile page. A unique 
							and random access string is issued, for example <code>d9531cf490f9</code>. You (via your token) can then POST to this endpoint like, 
							<code>/d/d9531cf490f9</code>. 
						</p>
						<p>
							Anyone can <strong>GET</strong> data from this endpoint without supplying a token.
						</p>
						
						<br>
						<h4>
							Vanity public endpoints
						</h4>
						<p>
							Vanity public endpoints can be registered on a first come first served basis.
						</p>
						
